msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:18
msgid "Exploring the API"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:20
msgid ""
"Navigate to [https://acc.cprmv.open-regels.nl/docs]{1}. The Swagger UI shows "
"all available endpoints with their parameters and response schemas. Click "
"**Try it out** on any endpoint to send a live request."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:24
msgid "Your first request"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:26
msgid ""
"The simplest call fetches a complete article from Dutch national law. Use "
"the `/rules/{rule_id_path}` endpoint:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:28
msgid ""
"GET https://acc.cprmv.open-regels.nl/rules/BWBR0015703_2025-07-"
"01_0%2C%20Artikel%2020"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:32
msgid ""
"`BWBR0015703_2025-07-01_0` is the rule set identifier (the Wet op de "
"Zorgtoeslag, version from 1 July 2025, index 0). `Artikel 20` is the rule "
"identifier within that set. The comma separator must be URL-encoded as `%2C`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:34
msgid ""
"The default `format=cprmv-json` response returns the full article including "
"all its nested paragraphs (`lid`) and sub-clauses (`onderdeel`)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:38
msgid "Fetching the current version of a law"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:40
msgid ""
"You do not need to know the publication date and index. Use a bare BWB "
"identifier to get the version valid today:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:42
msgid "GET https://acc.cprmv.open-regels.nl/rules/BWBR0015703"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:46
msgid "Or specify a date for which you want the valid version:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:48
msgid ""
"GET https://acc.cprmv.open-regels.nl/rules/BWBR0015703_2025-07-02_latest"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:54
msgid "Checking the CPRMV specification"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:56
msgid "The CPRMV specification in ReSpec format is served at:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:58
msgid "https://acc.cprmv.open-regels.nl/respec/"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:62
msgid ""
"This describes the full vocabulary — classes, properties, and cardinality "
"constraints — that the API's output conforms to."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:66
msgid "Checking supported methods"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:68
msgid "GET https://acc.cprmv.open-regels.nl/methods?format=turtle"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:72
msgid ""
"Returns the Methods Knowledge Graph in Turtle format, listing all registered "
"analysis methods, publication methods, and reference methods with their "
"configuration properties."
msgstr ""
